channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: US Marshal Shoots Wannabe Carjacker Outside Justice Sotomayor's DC Home
Haley urges her convention delegates to support Trump: 'Republican unity'
item.description: Former South Carolina Gov. Nikki Haley is releasing all of her delegates to next week's Republican National Convention and urging them to support former President Trump.

item.title: Sailor Punished After Searching for Biden's Medical Records
item.description: An unidentified junior sailor has been administratively punished and remains in the service after trying to access President Joe Biden's restricted medical records through a government database search in February, the U.S. Navy reported Thursday.

item.title: Gun Rights Groups Sue California Over Ridiculous Gun Tax
Tight-lipped House Dems still divided on Biden, leave closed-door meeting without consensus
item.description: House Democrats held a closed door meeting on Tuesday to discuss their concerns and thoughts about President Biden's candidacy for re-election.

item.title: Nikki Haley Releases Delegates, Urges Trump Vote
item.description: Former South Carolina Gov. Nikki Haley said Tuesday she will release the 97 delegates she gathered during her race for the GOP nomination and urge them to vote for former President Donald Trump next week at the Republican National Convention in Milwaukee.

item.title: Momentum: Haley Releases Her 97 Delegates, Urges Them to Vote for Trump
Judge McAfee gets $150 campaign donation from Trump co-defendant in Fani Willis case
item.description: A co-defendant in the Georgia racketeering case against former President Trump donated to the 2024 campaign of the Atlanta judge presiding over the case, according to news reports.

item.title: Speaker Johnson Rips Dems for Opposing SAVE Act
item.description: House Speaker Mike Johnson, R-La., chided Democrats for opposing the Safeguard American Voter Eligibility Act, which would prevent from noncitizens from voting in federal elections.

item.title: Former Dem Presidential Candidate Bob Kerrey Calls Biden Campaign Fealty Demand a 'Mistake'
State Department denies report Blinken told German chancellor Biden had to go to bed early at G-7 meeting
item.description: State Department denies reports that Secretary Antony Blinken told German chancellor that President Biden could not attend a meeting following a G-7 summit due to needing to go to bed.

item.title: AP Poll: Abortion Access 'for Any Reason' Gaining Support
item.description: A growing number of Americans support access to abortion "for any reason," according to a new poll from The Associated Press and NORC Center for Public Affairs Research released on Tuesday.

item.title: John Deere Exposed: Famous American Company Soaked in Disgusting Wokeness According to New Report
New White House digital staffer cheered social media ban on Trump: 'What took them so long?'
item.description: The White House recently hired a staffer who praised social media platforms for banning former President Trump after the Jan. 6 riot at the Capitol.

item.title: Emerson Poll: Trump Maintains 3 Point Lead Over Biden
item.description: Former President Donald Trump holds a 3-point lead over President Joe Biden, according to an Emerson College poll released Tuesday.
